‘You know yourself when you’re ready and you’re able to play and I feel just as good now, if not better, than I have ever done in my career.

‘Fitness-wise I’m right there. It’s just a case of getting the matches and proving it to everyone else as well.’

Gordon spent a lengthy spell last season training with Rangers at Murray Park and had an offer from first club Hearts before Celtic entered the fray.

